snippet.title: Johnny Depp and Amber Heard Video Apology Over Dogs
snippet.description:
Actors Johnny Depp and Amber Heard apologized to Australian authorities for not declaring their dogs on an immigration document last year. Australia has very strict biosecurity laws to protect the health  people, animals and plants. Everyone entering the country must truthfully declare if they are carrying any items listed on the Incoming Passenger Card.

Ms Amber Heard appeared in court to answer charges alleging the illegal importation of her two dogs into Australia in April 2015.

Ms Heard pleaded guilty to one count of producing a false document (her Incoming Passenger Card).

Ms Heard also offered to publicly state her apology with the support of her husband in this video.
